{"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Composing Large Games","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContents","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin"],"anchor":"Composing-Large-Games"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Package a reusable game system as an importable unit of verbs and rules."}],"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" let a game split its "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"own","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" world across types and packages. A "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"plugin","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" goes one step further: it packages a reusable game "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"system","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" — commerce, combat, dialog, magic — as an importable unit of verbs and rules that any game can opt into. Instead of hand-copying the same "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"buy"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sell"},{"type":"text","text":" logic into every shop game, you write it once as a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and splice it in."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A plugin is "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"logic only"}]},{"type":"text","text":". It contributes the player-typeable vocabulary a system needs and the rules that react to it, but it owns no rooms, items, or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":" state of its own. It operates over entities and state the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"host"}]},{"type":"text","text":" game declares, receiving what it needs as parameters. That’s what keeps it portable — it assumes nothing about the host’s world beyond the traits and intents they agree on."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"A plugin is a `GamePlugin`","anchor":"A-plugin-is-a-GamePlugin","level":2},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct CommercePlugin: GamePlugin {","    static let buy = Intent(\"buy\")","    static let sell = Intent(\"sell\")","","    var verbs: [SyntaxRule] {","        SyntaxRule(\"buy\",  slots: .direct, intent: Self.buy)","        SyntaxRule(\"sell\", slots: .direct, intent: Self.sell)","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"verbs"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"type":"text","text":" both default to empty, so a plugin declares only what it needs. Exposing the intents as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"static let"},{"type":"text","text":" constants lets host rules name the same intents the verbs emit."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"The host splices verbs and rules","anchor":"The-host-splices-verbs-and-rules","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The host stores the plugin as a plain property and splices its vocabulary into its own "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"verbs"},{"type":"text","text":" block. A plain plugin property is neither a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item"},{"type":"text","text":", nor "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":", so the bootstrap’s reflection walk ignores it — it never becomes an entity and never collides."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct LampShop: Game {","    let commerce = CommercePlugin()","    @Global var purse = Purse(coins: 10)          \/\/ the HOST owns the wallet","    let lantern = Item { name(\"brass lantern\"); trait(\"price\", 5) }","","    var verbs: [SyntaxRule] { commerce.verbs }    \/\/ splice the vocabulary","    \/\/ rules below","}"]},{"type":"heading","text":"Parameterized rules over host entities","anchor":"Parameterized-rules-over-host-entities","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The plugin’s rules need the host’s own lantern and purse — things it can’t know about in advance. So rules that touch host state are exposed as "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"parameterized methods"}]},{"type":"text","text":" returning "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Rules"},{"type":"text","text":", which the host calls with its own declarations. The wallet is handed in as closures that read and adjust the host’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":"; they run under the live turn, so they see and mutate state exactly as an inline rule would."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["extension CommercePlugin {","    @RuleBuilder","    func purchase(","        of item: Item,","        balance: @escaping @Sendable () -> Int,","        charge:  @escaping @Sendable (Int) -> Void","    ) -> Rules {","        item.before(Self.buy) {","            let price = item.trait(\"price\", as: Int.self) ?? 0","            guard balance() >= price else {","                try refuse(\"You can't afford the \\(item.name); it costs \\(price) coins.\")","            }","            charge(price)","            try reply(\"You buy the \\(item.name) for \\(price) coins. You have \\(balance()) left.\")","        }","    }","}","","\/\/ in the host:","var rules: Rules {","    commerce.purchase(of: lantern,","                      balance: { purse.coins },","                      charge:  { purse.coins -= $0 })","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The protocol’s own "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"type":"text","text":" requirement is for self-contained, world-scoped rules that need nothing from the host; anything host-specific goes through a factory method like this."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"A plugin can contribute only vocabulary","anchor":"A-plugin-can-contribute-only-vocabulary","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The rules are optional. A plugin can teach the parser a word and leave the behavior to the host, which handles the shared intent in its own "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct Appraiser: GamePlugin {","    var verbs: [SyntaxRule] {","        SyntaxRule(\"appraise\", slots: .direct, intent: Intent(\"appraise\"))","    }","}","","\/\/ in the host:","var rules: Rules {","    gem.before(Intent(\"appraise\")) {","        try reply(\"The \\(gem.name) is worth \\(gem.trait(\"price\", as: Int.self) ?? 0) coins.\")","    }","}"]},{"type":"heading","text":"Content-bearing plugins own their region","anchor":"Content-bearing-plugins-own-their-region","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A logic-only "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin"},{"type":"text","text":" declares no world of its own — it operates entirely over entities the host passes it. A plugin that needs to ship its "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"own"}]},{"type":"text","text":" rooms, items, and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":" state is a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles"},{"type":"text","text":" instead: a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent"},{"type":"text","text":" carries "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"verbs"},{"type":"text","text":", and the bootstrap discovers its entities by reflection, "},{"type":"reference","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"namespacing"}],"isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"namespacing","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles#EntityIDs-are-namespaced-by-the-bundle"},{"type":"text","text":" them under the bundle so a reusable plugin can’t collide with the host. List it in the game’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"content"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The two roles compose in one type. A single struct can conform to "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent"},{"type":"text","text":" (for its auto-namespaced region and self-contained rules) "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"and"}]},{"type":"text","text":" expose host-facing rule factories exactly like a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin"},{"type":"text","text":" — factories are just methods returning "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Rules"},{"type":"text","text":", so any type can offer them:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct ShrineContent: GameContent {","    static let donate = Intent(\"donate\")","","    let shrine = Location { name(\"Stone Shrine\"); description(\"…\") }   \/\/ its own room","    @Global var visits = 0                                             \/\/ its own state","","    var verbs: [SyntaxRule] { SyntaxRule(\"donate\", slots: .direct, intent: Self.donate) }","    var rules: Rules { shrine.onEnter { visits += 1; try reply(\"…\") } }  \/\/ self-contained","","    \/\/ Host-facing factory over a host item + host global — the GamePlugin pattern.","    func offering(of item: Item,","                  merit: @escaping @Sendable () -> Int,","                  credit: @escaping @Sendable (Int) -> Void) -> Rules {","        item.before(Self.donate) { credit(item.trait(\"value\", as: Int.self) ?? 0)","            try reply(\"Your merit rises to \\(merit()).\") }","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The host lists it in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"content"},{"type":"text","text":" (registering the namespaced region) "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"and"}]},{"type":"text","text":" splices the factory into its own "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"text":", wiring it to host declarations:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct PilgrimGame: Game {","    let shrineKit = ShrineContent()","    @Global var merit = 0","    let coin = Item { name(\"brass coin\"); trait(\"value\", 7) }","","    var content: GameContents { shrineKit }","    var verbs: [SyntaxRule] { shrineKit.verbs }","    var rules: Rules {","        shrineKit.offering(of: coin, merit: { merit }, credit: { merit += $0 })","    }","    \/\/ map: place coin in shrineKit.shrine, wire plaza ↔ shrineKit.shrine, …","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"References stay token-based across the boundary, so a host item can sit in a plugin room and a plugin rule can hook a host entity regardless of the namespace.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Worked examples","anchor":"Worked-examples","level":2},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Tests\/GnustoTests\/Support\/CommerceGame.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" — the logic-only commerce plugin ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"buy"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sell"},{"type":"text","text":" verbs, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"purchase"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sale"},{"type":"text","text":" factories, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"LampShop"},{"type":"text","text":" host); "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PluginTests"},{"type":"text","text":" drives a buy\/sell turn end to end."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Tests\/GnustoTests\/Support\/ShrineContent.swift"},{"type":"text","text":" — the content-bearing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ShrineContent"},{"type":"text","text":" plugin (owns a namespaced shrine region "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"and"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" exposes an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"offering"},{"type":"text","text":" factory) with its "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PilgrimGame"},{"type":"text","text":" host; "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ContentPluginTests"},{"type":"text","text":" drives a donate turn across the namespace boundary and checks the namespacing."}]}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gnusto\/plugins"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto"]]},"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Plugins","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"role":"article","title":"Plugins","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"Gnusto"}]},"references":{"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/ContentBundles#EntityIDs-are-namespaced-by-the-bundle":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles#EntityIDs-are-namespaced-by-the-bundle","title":"EntityIDs are namespaced by the bundle","abstract":[],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/contentbundles#EntityIDs-are-namespaced-by-the-bundle","type":"topic","kind":"section"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Swift engine for writing parser-driven interactive fiction — text adventures in the tradition of Zork and Infocom’s ZIL."}],"title":"Gnusto"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles":{"role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles","type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"Splitting a Game Across Files","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Keep a large game readable by composing its map and rules from per-region helpers."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/splittingagameacrossfiles"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GameContents":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContents","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"GameContents","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContents"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The collected content bundles a game declares, in declaration order."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gamecontents","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContents"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Item":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"Item","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Item"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A thing in the world."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/item","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Item"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Location":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"Location","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Location"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A place in the world."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/location","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Location"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GamePlugin":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"GamePlugin","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GamePlugin"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A reusable game system — commerce, combat, dialog, magic — packaged as an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"importable unit of "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"verbs"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"rules"}]},{"type":"text","text":", that a host game opts into."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gameplugin","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GamePlugin"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Rules":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Rules","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"Rules","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Rules"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The collected rules of a game, declared in one "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"type":"text","text":" block. Large games"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"compose: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"var rules: Rules { cloakRules; barRules }"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/rules","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Rules"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GameContent":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"GameContent","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContent"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A self-contained slice of a game’s world: its own rooms, items, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":" state, plus the geography, rules, and verbs that go with them."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gamecontent","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContent"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/ContentBundles":{"role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"Content Bundles","abstract":[{"text":"Give a region its own declarations — its own type, and even its own package.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/contentbundles"}}}